The path forward is clear: Medicare negotiation is THE number one way to lower the cost of prescription drugs! #LetMedicareNegotiate

If you needed insulin, you would have paid three times more with Medicare than under the VA in 2017.
 
List price of Lantus (insulin): $250.24
VA-negotiated price for the same drug: $76.74

Unlike the VA and private health care plans, Medicare is not allowed to negotiate for lower prices. Medicare could have saved $14.4 billion on just 50 drugs in 2016 if the program had paid the same prices as the VA!

TUNE IN as @SenKlobuchar @PattyMurray @ChrisMurphyCT and I make clear that Medicare should be able to use its own purchasing power to negotiate lower drug prices! #LetMedicareNegotiate https://twitter.com/i/broadcasts/1BdGYAPMLyoGX …

I’m a cosponsor of @SenatorBaldwin’s important bill that would stop these short-term health plans. If Senate Republicans are serious about protecting people with pre-existing conditions, then they should pass this bill – now!

Short term health plans make comprehensive health insurance less and less affordable. People like Tiffany should be able to focus on getting the treatment they need to live their best life possible, not how they’ll pay for the insurance they need.

Tiffany's tumor has recurred 6 times. She's been through 7 surgeries, chemotherapy, and radiation treatments. She's lost some use of her left arm and hand. Tiffany doesn't have a choice - her life depends on having comprehensive health insurance.
More than half of people in Michigan have a pre-existing condition. That includes people like Tiffany from Livonia, who was just 17 when she was diagnosed with a brain tumor.

A recent study found that NONE of these plans covered maternity care. Why is the Administration pushing plans that don’t offer this basic coverage when we have a maternal health care crisis in this country?

Tune in as my friend @SenatorBaldwin highlights the importance of stopping the Administration’s expansion of health care plans that DON’T have protections for pre-existing conditions and DON'T cover essential health benefits like maternity care or mental health treatment! https://twitter.com/SenatorBaldwin/status/1136376137590947841 …
